post_text: The deadline to apply for P-EBT food benefits has been extended to July 31. Eligible families can apply for this one-time food benefit. Children who received free or reduced-price school meals through the National School Lunch Program during the 2019-2020 school year are eligible for P-EBT. Eligible families should have received the application link from their school. Eligible families that received SNAP benefits for March have already received P-EBT benefits and do not have to apply. If you did not receive an application link or if you need help filling out the P-EBT application, please contact the P-EBT Call Center at 833-613-6220. The public charge rule does not apply to P-EBT benefits.
text: The deadline to apply for P-EBT food benefits has been extended to July 31. Eligible families can apply for this one-time food benefit. Children who received free or reduced-price school meals through the National School Lunch Program during the 2019-2020 school year are eligible for P-EBT. Eligible families should have received the application link from their school. Eligible families that received SNAP benefits for March have already received P-EBT benefits and do not have to apply. If you did not receive an application link or if you need help filling out the P-EBT application, please contact the P-EBT Call Center at 833-613-6220. The public charge rule does not apply to P-EBT benefits.

Dawson ISD is participating in the Summer Feeding Program Through July 31st.
They will be serving grab and go boxes twice a week for curbside pick up. Meal Pick up will be at
Dawson Elementary and the Purdon Fire Department every Tuesday and Friday from 11:00am until 1:00pm. The meal sites are open to all children 18 and under (21 and under if special needs)

Children do NOT have to be enrolled at Dawson ISD.
to receive meals.

Dawson ISD is providing free breakfast, lunch, and suppers to cover the entire week.

Tuesday's box will provide 3 breakfast,3 lunches and 3 suppers.
Friday's box will provide 4 breakfast, 4 lunches, and 4 suppers.

If you need meals delivered please text 903-229-2066 with your name, address and how many children and we will schedule you for delivery.

post_text: OH THE ANXIETY!
shared_text:
YOUTUBE.COM
Episode 102 - Dots

Counselor's Corner
April 28 at 9:56 PM ¬∑

HOW. MANY. TIMES. HAVE. I. BEEN. HERE!? Not just with a boy people in general. How many times have I written a text just to delete it and retype it. Then deleted it again. Or I have sat waiting on the edge of my seat for someone to respond. As I wait anxiety eats away at me....did I say something wrong? Did I spell it all correctly? Did I use the wrong your, you're? Do they not want to? Do they just feel bad for me? AHHHHHH!!!!

post_text: Mrs. Duke's anxiety guidance lesson for junior high and high school üíô
shared_text:
Counselor's Corner
April 28 at 9:47 PM ¬∑

Junior High and High School are hard...there's the pressure you put on yourself. The pressure you get from your teachers. Pressure from your parents. And then friends. Anxiety and worry can drown all logical thoughts. I'm 35 years old and I can let the smallest comment - or lack of a comment make my head begin to swim with self doubt or loathing. I understand and I'm here.

This is a guidance lesson on anxiety that I was going to do with you this month....for state testing and life purposes. I wanted you to still be able to see my words and maybe in a moment of panic they will bring you comfort. I love you.

post_text: Well...the news from the Governor today was kind of devastating. We at least wanted the last 3 weeks in May to rap things up and say our good byes before summer. We wanted some finality for our seniors! I understand it was done out of caution, but it‚Äôs not easy. I have been inundated by staff stating the same sentiments, and suggestions on how we can possibly end our year on a high note. I assure you the administration will meet next week to get a game plan together. A few things are in the works already. Keep sending suggestions, and we will pass on the information as soon as possible. We love our students! Stay Bulldog strong! We will persevere! #bulldogpride #seniors2020

shared_text:
Arkansas SkyDome Planetarium
April 5 at 8:18 PM ¬∑

April 7th - CLOSEST FULL MOON OF 2020

The moon reaches perigee, or its closest point to the Earth for this orbit, on Tuesday afternoon at 1:15pm. A few hours later, at 9:35pm, the moon reaches full. This cosmic coincidence makes this the closest Full Moon of the year. At that time the moon will be 220,160 miles from Earth, compared to the average 238,000.

Tuesday night look overhead to see the closest, brightest full moon of 2020. The moon will rise about 7:25pm.

I will never walk away and I will always find you.

Wortham High School has an awesome CTE department!

What departments are considered CTE (Career and Technical Education)?

Agriculture Education featuring Mrs. Bean and Mr. Calame!
Family and Consumer Science (formally called Home Economics) featuring Miss Davis!
Technology and Business Education featuring Mrs. Boyd!
Accounting with Mr. Rex!

We also have other support teachers like Mrs. Myers in Forensics, Ms. Bearden inBusiness English, and Mr. Barnett in Professional Communication!

Stay tuned for more!

post_text:
Did you know?????
February is CTE month!

CTE or career and technology education is a term applied to schools, institutions, and educational programs that specialize in the skilled trades, applied sciences, modern technologies, and career preparation.

CTE was formerly called vocational education.

In a nutshell, CTE is designed to prepare students for work!

Wortham High School has a super CTE department with incredible teachers!!!

Stay tuned for more!

post_text: October is National Anti-Bullying Month. Bullying prevention remains one of Wortham ISD's top priorities. In order to help educate and raise awareness of bullying prevention, WISD actively acknowledges National Bullying Prevention month in October. Parents please speak with your students about the ramifications of bullying. Encourage them to be the change agent needed to help put an end to this. Be a friend, not a bully! #bulldogsagainstbullying
